@node LastNotes "LAST NOTES"


                                @{fg shine}LAST NOTES@{fg text}


This programme was done a year ago, in February 2002. At that time, it was
on the brink of being released. All was left to do was to give it a name
and release it, but for some reasons it's never been so and I just left it
lost in my HD. I now decide to release it but I'm afraid it'll be nameless.
Also, since I've written this documentation, things have moved on a bit and
my introductory comments on internationalization on Amiga are a bit out of
date: a piece of software for using Unicode has been developped by Ken
Shillito. Hopefully, his work will go on and important applications with
international potential (web browsers, YAM, ...) will become aware of
exotic writings, like an option to specify the encoding system for outgoing
mails in YAM. Well, as for me, I'm done. Not that I don't want to work
anymore on this, but I don't see much point at the moment. If people have
suggestions, I'll be glad to look on them. If I could be of any help to add
Chinese capabilities to mailers like YAM, count me in.

I included in this archive fonts that aren't mine and which have been found
in the Chinese software I tried (see @{"Authors" LINK Authors}). I modified
one of them. I hope it's not much of a concern. These two programmes have
been released years ago and I gave link to them, so I guess it's fair
enough.

Also included are a few GB2312 texts which can be of interest about Chinese
characters. They've been found from various internet sources.

That's it, I'm off. Till next time, @{i}zai jian!@{ui}

February 2003

@endnode
